        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 10:17AM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 1017 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Blanchester,
moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and very heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Visibility will be poor and hydroplaning
is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Washington Court House, Wilmington, Hillsboro, Georgetown,
Blanchester, Mount Orab, Waynesville, Bethel, Sabina, Williamsburg,
Lynchburg, Leesburg, New Vienna, Morrow, Winchester, Sardinia,
Seaman, Felicity, Belfast, and Rocky Fork Point.

This includes I-71 in Ohio between mile markers 36 and 57.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

Motorists should slow down and use extra caution.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
